cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with object detection in medical images using region proposal networks and attention mechanisms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel selective attention approach, which involves modifying the pyramid of regression references in the RPN, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of organ- and modality-specific information, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with medical images, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the use of imaging protocol information, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
